text: Obviously (?) betfairutil is just using betfairlightweight to read a series of market books; prices_file_to_data_frame is concatenating a series of data frames, one for each market book. text:
Hello guys, I have a problem with cashing out through betfairlightweight.

When I need to close a position, I execute an opposite entry calculating the size in relation to the price.

If I make a request to see the open positions, I get 2 positions instead of 0. How can I only see the positions that are actually still open, discarding those where I carried out the cash out?

text:
Lot of water to flow under the bridge between now and then. Even if it happens in April, we would need more clarity on what happens to accounts that refuse or fail an affordability check - is account closed, are deposites limited to £10 a month? Nobody knows so it's really hard to even guess.

That said, I can't believe that at some point some Tories will get some badgering from "influential" people within the horse racing industry concerned about the impact this nonsense would have on British racing. What has been proposed all seems very half arsed and anyone with a shred of common sense can see that the changes will do nothing at all to address the issues that the anti-gambling lobbyists claim to be concerned about.
